# Vue 3 Composition API

All Vue components must use the Composition API with `<script setup lang="ts">`.

- Never use the Options API (`data`, `methods`, `computed` properties as options, etc.).
- Never use `defineComponent()` — use `<script setup>` instead.
- Use `defineProps`, `defineEmits`, and `defineExpose` compiler macros directly.
- Extract reusable logic into composables (`use*.ts` files).

```vue
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<script lang="ts">
import { defineComponent } from 'vue';
export default defineComponent({
  data() { return { count: 0 }; },
  methods: { increment() { this.count++; } },
});
</script>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref } from 'vue';

const count = ref(0);
function increment() { count.value++; }
</script>
```
